post_cb({"28247047": {"ParentId": "28246988", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>There is no difference <em>in your example</em> to a <code>typedef</code>.</p>\n<p>Those are identical:</p>\n<pre><code>typedef int a;\nusing a = int;\n</code></pre>\n<p>In general, it is more versatile though, which is the reason it was introduced:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>It can be templated.</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;class X&gt; using smart = std::unique_ptr&lt;X&gt;;\n</code></pre></li>\n<li><p>It can be used to import symbols into the current scope.</p>\n<pre><code>struct Derived : Base {\n    using Base::Fun;\n};\n</code></pre></li>\n</ul>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3204551", "LastEditorUserId": "3204551", "LastEditDate": "2015-01-31T03:23:39.957", "Id": "28247047", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2015-01-31T01:03:17.180", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-31T03:23:39.957"}, "28246988": {"CommentCount": "2", "ViewCount": "78", "CreationDate": "2015-01-31T00:54:08.000", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-31T03:23:39.957", "Title": "Could someone explain the meaning of \"using\"?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "28247047", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "28246988", "Score": "2", "Body": "<p>I do not understand below usage of using in C++.\nWhat's difference with typedef?\nCould someone explain it with some example?</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;typename DataType&gt;\nclass DataWriter\n{\nusing ObjType = std::function&lt;void(DataType)&gt;\n// ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><using>", "OwnerUserId": "4459978", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "28247015": {"ParentId": "28246988", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>There is no difference. [dcl.typedef]/2:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_28246988_28247015_0\">A <em>typedef-name</em> can also be introduced by an <em>alias-declaration</em>. The\n  identifier following the <code>using</code> keyword becomes a <em>typedef-name</em>\n  [..]. <strong>It has the same semantics as if it were introduced by the\n  <code>typedef</code> specifier.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I.e.</p>\n<pre><code>using ObjType = std::function&lt;void(DataType)&gt;;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is equivalent to</p>\n<pre><code>typedef std::function&lt;void(DataType)&gt; ObjType;\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3647361", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "28247015", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2015-01-31T00:57:31.487", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-31T00:57:31.487"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_28246988_28247015_0": {"section_id": 5408, "quality": 0.9444444444444444, "length": 17}}, "n3337": {"so_28246988_28247015_0": {"section_id": 5203, "quality": 0.9444444444444444, "length": 17}}, "n4659": {"so_28246988_28247015_0": {"section_id": 6830, "quality": 0.9444444444444444, "length": 17}}}});